item_prototype.name: [{#SNMPVALUE}]_temperatureValue
item_prototype.description:
We use a unsigned int to prevent -1° Temperatures which are sometimes returned by the ReadyNAS. Seems to be a know problem in ReadyNAS SNMP implementation.
https://community.netgear.com/t5/ReadyNAS-in-Business/Insane-disk-temp-readings-from-ReadyNAS-3100/td-p/928290

trigger_prototype.expression: {Template SNMP ReadyNas 6.9.x:TemperatureValue[{#SNMPVALUE}].last()}<{Template SNMP ReadyNas 6.9.x:TemperatureMin[{#SNMPVALUE}].last()} or {Template SNMP ReadyNas 6.9.x:TemperatureValue[{#SNMPVALUE}].last()}>{Template SNMP ReadyNas 6.9.x:TemperatureMax[{#SNMPVALUE}].last()}
